<section xml:id="javadoc_vocabulary">
<title>Vocabulary</title>
<ul>
<li>
<title>documentation:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>documentation</h></idx>
Comments that describe the technical operation of a class or method.</p></li>
<li>
<title>Javadoc:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>Javadoc</h></idx>
A tool that reads Java source code and generates documentation in HTML format.</p></li>
<li>
<title>signature:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>signature</h></idx>
The first line of a method that defines its name and parameters.</p></li>
<li>
<title>tag:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>tag</h></idx>
A label that begins with an at sign (<c>@</c>) and is used by Javadoc to organize documentation into sections.</p></li>
<li>
<title>description:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>description</h></idx>
The first line of a documentation comment that explains what the class/method does.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
